Let $G_{\nu, b}(x)$ be the CDF of the first time a Bessel process with parameter
$\nu$ hits $b > 0$; this is given in \cite{hamanamatsumoto13}. Then the CDF of
$\xi$ is $F(x) = \left(1 - G_{\frac{d}{2} - 1, x}(1)\right)^2$, where $d$ is the
dimension of the Bessel process.

The table above was thus formed by first using numerical methods to compute the
values of the CDF of $\xi$ at select $d$ and $p$ and using root-finding
techniques to find, for a fixed $d$, the value $k$ such that $p = P(\xi > k)$.

